The paper discusses open problems in the analysis of boolean functions, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as related fields. Additionally, some of the open problems involve geometric aspects of boolean functions, which could be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG).
